{"id":13630,"date":"2020-11-11T12:13:05","date_gmt":"2020-11-11T12:13:05","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/defyhatenow.org\/?p=13630"},"modified":"2020-11-11T12:30:16","modified_gmt":"2020-11-11T12:30:16","slug":"peacejam2020-shaping-peace-together","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/defyhatenow.org\/peacejam2020-shaping-peace-together\/","title":{"rendered":"#PEACEJAM2020 &#8211;  Shaping peace together"},"content":{"rendered":"<p>The 21st of September is the UN International Day of Peace. Each year on this day the peace initiative #defyhatenow organises a #peacejam aimed at reinforcing peacebuilding efforts and creating a network for diverse actors in the peacebuilding process to share ideas.<\/p>\n<p><b>A #Peacejam is an informal gathering of people, usually online, that includes\u00a0 activities and performances, such as\u00a0 music, poetry, and open forum discussions,\u00a0 with the\u00a0 aim of supporting peacebuilding.\u00a0<\/b><\/p>\n<p>This year&#8217;s International Peace Day came together\u00a0 under the theme of <i>Shaping Peace Together, <\/i>echoing\u00a0 one of the r0g agency\u2019s core philosophies of DIWO (Do It With Others).<\/p>\n<p>#Defyhatenow crafted this year\u2019s Peace Day #peacejam with a special focus on creating digital ecosystems that aid\u00a0 cooperation amongst peacebuilders. Social media plays an important role in shaping, sharing in, and building peace efforts through fostering safe digital spaces that allow\u00a0 people from different backgrounds to share their ideas about peace.<\/p>\n<p>In the context of this years #peacejam, which was held as a live stream conference, CSOs, partners of #defyhatenow, along with the general public, discussed issues relating to\u00a0 trauma healing, the role of social media in conflict and peacebuilding, and the specific role and challenges of women and girls in peacebuilding.<\/p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-13632\" src=\"https:\/\/defyhatenow.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/11\/screen-capture.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"512\" height=\"295\" \/><\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<p>Other activities that took place in the context of the #peacejam included:<\/p>\n<p><b>#paint4peace<\/b>, in which people posted photos of themselves\u00a0 holding up signs of peace and posted these under\u00a0 #peacejam2020<\/p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"aligncenter wp-image-13096\" src=\"https:\/\/defyhatenow.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/09\/painting-a-picture-4peace-together_rev.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"536\" height=\"347\" srcset=\"https:\/\/defyhatenow.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/09\/painting-a-picture-4peace-together_rev.png 1666w, https:\/\/defyhatenow.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/09\/painting-a-picture-4peace-together_rev-744x482.png 744w, https:\/\/defyhatenow.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/09\/painting-a-picture-4peace-together_rev-1030x668.png 1030w, https:\/\/defyhatenow.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/09\/painting-a-picture-4peace-together_rev-768x498.png 768w, https:\/\/defyhatenow.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/09\/painting-a-picture-4peace-together_rev-1536x996.png 1536w, https:\/\/defyhatenow.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/09\/painting-a-picture-4peace-together_rev-1500x972.png 1500w, https:\/\/defyhatenow.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/09\/painting-a-picture-4peace-together_rev-705x457.png 705w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 536px) 100vw, 536px\" \/><\/p>\n<p><a href=\"https:\/\/defyhatenow.org\/shaping-peace-together-art4peace\/\"><b>#Art4Peace;<\/b><\/a> highlighting the importance of art in peacebuilding efforts. <a href=\"https:\/\/defyhatenow.org\/shaping-peace-together-art4peace\/\">https:\/\/defyhatenow.org\/shaping-peace-together-art4peace\/<\/a><\/p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"aligncenter wp-image-13240\" src=\"https:\/\/defyhatenow.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/09\/119558223_2829450017333717_3941629363459589410_o.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"554\" height=\"554\" srcset=\"https:\/\/defyhatenow.org\/wp-con